Japan's NHK apologises over talk show guest's Hitler T-shirt.
Japans public broadcaster NHK has apologized over a cartoon with Adolph Hitlers face that was printed on a T-shirt worn by a talk show guest.The black T-shirt worn by entrepreneur Takafumi Horie also carried a No war message on one side and a peace symbol on a lapel. Horie was a guest Wednesday on NHKs Afternoon Live daily talk show.The T-shirt has prompted complaints from viewers. During the program, the NHK announcer and the shows co-host apologized.Responding to a tweet asking about the Hitler cartoon, Horie said it was meant to be an anti-war message.